1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:07,850 --> 00:00:08,750
Dude, awesome!

3
00:00:09,620 --> 00:00:10,860
Marek, what are you doing here?

4
00:00:11,060 --> 00:00:12,640
I've got a son, you know that?

5
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:15,750
Well, congratulations!

6
00:00:17,330 --> 00:00:18,870
And is the mother doing okay?

7
00:00:18,870 --> 00:00:23,550
Yeah, thanks for asking, well you know, she's in a retirement home now, but she's loving it there.

8
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:26,450
Wait, why are you bringing my mom into this?

9
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:28,910
No, I meant the mother of the child.

10
00:00:28,910 --> 00:00:29,370
Oh, Jaruna!

11
00:00:29,850 --> 00:00:30,990
Yeah, she's fine too.

12
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:34,250
I just need someone to watch the kid.

13
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,250
Just for the weekend.

14
00:00:37,650 --> 00:00:39,750
God, I can't babysit an infant.

15
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:42,070
What infant, man?

16
00:00:42,950 --> 00:00:44,150
He's nine.

17
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:45,250
I thought it was something recent.

18
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:49,310
Well, in a way it is recent.

19
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:53,050
I haven't really checked my mail for the last nine years.

20
00:00:54,550 --> 00:00:56,450
But the important thing is it's a boy.

21
00:00:57,150 --> 00:00:58,410
A tough guy like me.

22
00:00:58,450 --> 00:00:59,150
You get it, right?

23
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:00,910
I have a daughter.

24
00:01:01,010 --> 00:01:02,490
Yeah, I've got a few of those somewhere too.

25
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:05,850
But a man's gotta take care of a boy.

26
00:01:07,550 --> 00:01:13,050
It's just that today everything went sideways, I'm stuck with the kid and I just got this gig.

27
00:01:15,050 --> 00:01:18,150
The Americans are shooting a Lassie remake.

28
00:01:20,050 --> 00:01:21,350
I'm doing the trainer.

29
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,850
You understand, you don't turn down a chance like this.

30
00:01:26,850 --> 00:01:28,780
Yeah, I get it, but I...

31
00:01:34,550 --> 00:01:36,250
Marek, that was a minute.

32
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,250
I'm not going to Slapy with you anymore.

33
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:45,050
Fine.

34
00:02:11,650 --> 00:02:12,940
Hold on, please, babe.

35
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,850
Five minutes, I promise.

36
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:16,550
Okay, I'm setting my watch.

37
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:17,640
Bye.

38
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:22,880
Look, I get it, I'm a man too, but it really won't work.

39
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,340
You can't leave me in the lurch.

40
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:27,350
His mother is turning him into a total softie.

41
00:02:28,050 --> 00:02:29,250
Can you imagine?

42
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:32,850
She makes him drink cocoa for breakfast.

43
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:35,530
Luckily he spits it out, takes after me.

44
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:39,730
But she already got him to carry a yellow pencil case with the Greenpeace logo.

45
00:02:40,650 --> 00:02:44,650
I try to make a man out of him on weekends, but today it really won't work.

46
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:46,750
Marek, sorry.

47
00:02:48,550 --> 00:02:49,450
You owe me.

48
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:54,700
Well, if you mean that New Year's Eve at the TV station before the taping, I actually had that under control.

49
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:56,050
Yeah, under control.

50
00:02:57,150 --> 00:03:02,950
When I got to that party, the fat guys from Zizkov were holding you by the legs and Zazvorkova was shoving your head into a bowl.

51
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,710
We were arguing whether I could sing backwards.

52
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:07,110
It doesn't matter what you were arguing about.

53
00:03:07,130 --> 00:03:10,810
The point is, if I hadn't shown up, the whole nation would've seen you with toilet paper on your head.

54
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:14,500
Marek, it really won't work, it's...

55
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,200
It will.

56
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:20,850
Because luckily, there's still Bruiser Tom.

57
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:22,680
Who?

58
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:24,060
You.

59
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:31,950
I spent all day explaining to him that there's only one man in the world who's tougher than me.

60
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:37,350
He's dying to meet you.

61
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:41,160
Marek, I'm more of an old fuddy-duddy.

62
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,600
Nonsense, you're a hero!

63
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:47,850
The kid was begging me on his knees for a weekend with you.

64
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:50,910
And what am I supposed to tell him now?

65
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:53,650
That he's not good enough for Bruiser Tom?

66
00:03:54,050 --> 00:03:57,850
Or even that there's no such thing as Bruiser Tom?

67
00:03:58,350 --> 00:04:04,340
That there's just an uncle who sips cocoa and nibbles cookies in a musty little shop full of sheet music?

68
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:06,650
Is that what you want?

69
00:04:07,950 --> 00:04:08,350
He'd probably get over it somehow.

70
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:18,150
How did you feel when they told you there's no Santa Claus?

71
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:20,850
Awful.

72
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:22,480
Exactly.

73
00:04:23,580 --> 00:04:25,240
No worries, man.

74
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:27,480
The kid is absolutely zero trouble.

75
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,120
He's earning scout badges.

76
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:31,060
Right now he's deflating the tires on every car in the street.

77
00:04:32,050 --> 00:04:33,940
Nature conservation badge.

78
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,240
Got a problem with that?

79
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,360
No, I park in the courtyard.

80
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:39,280
Well there you go, nothing to worry about.

81
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:44,350
Look, he's got this little notebook for it, you just stamp it each time.

82
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:49,800
Chief!

83
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:50,800
Awesome, Bull!

84
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:54,150
Yeah!

85
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:56,850
Now watch this.

86
00:04:58,150 --> 00:05:01,550
This is Bruiser Tom.

87
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,340
I can really stay here with him?

88
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:08,520
You bet.

89
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:10,450
Marek.

90
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:13,960
Fine, alright.

91
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:14,520
Yeah!

92
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:17,060
I won't let you down, Bruiser.

93
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:17,300
Yeah!

94
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:19,950
Oh damn.

95
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:20,980
Outlet.

96
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,840
Yeah, yeah.

97
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:25,940
There's a bomb at Slapy.

98
00:05:26,450 --> 00:05:32,260
When it blows, the only thing sticking out of flooded Prague will be the Zizkov TV tower antenna.

99
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:33,650
Damn terrorists.

100
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:38,650
I'm sorry, guys, but someone's gotta sort them out.

101
00:05:39,850 --> 00:05:40,650
You know everything?

102
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:41,480
Stay safe.

103
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,250
I'll rip the detonator, Dad.

104
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,150
I think it'll work without that.

105
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,200
Bye!

106
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:58,250
Will you sign my nature conservation badge?

107
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,280
Why are the cars in the courtyard all flat?

108
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:14,650
There's nothing here either.

109
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,950
You really can't buy her anything?

110
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:20,550
Mom says if we had money for gifts, we should just give it to her directly.

111
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:25,050
And our piggy bank is empty anyway, because the gas bill came.

112
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:26,750
What did you give her last year?

113
00:06:27,050 --> 00:06:28,250
A giraffe made from chestnuts.

114
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:30,550
But she didn't really like it.

115
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:31,600
I see.

116
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:33,950
What's Lexa giving her?

117
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:36,310
Something that'll blow her away, for sure.

118
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:37,030
Really?

119
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:38,950
Last year he skipped lunch for a month.

120
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:45,050
Mom then bet Mr. Stodola she could go without eating longer than his python, and she won a snake fang.

121
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:49,990
Hey, sis.

122
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,650
So, got a gift yet?

123
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:54,660
Lexa, don't snatch.

124
00:06:55,050 --> 00:06:56,950
I've already got it figured out.

125
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:01,450
Iva, could I hide at your place until Sunday?

126
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:04,150
No way.

127
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:05,050
Damn.

128
00:07:06,550 --> 00:07:08,150
Then I'll have to go to the cellar.

129
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,650
I'm giving Mom a weekend without me.

130
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:11,810
Lexa!

131
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:13,650
What, wanna play?

132
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:17,450
Give her that too, you can stay with us.

133
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:21,350
Mom says if she has two kids, she wants two gifts.

134
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:23,950
Lexa, the cellar awaits.

135
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:32,330
Dad?

136
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,150
Bruiser what?

137
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,250
He must be crazy.

138
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:43,150
He yelled at me "you rat, if you snitch, I'll break both your arms."

139
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,750
So this is my den.

140
00:07:52,150 --> 00:07:52,610
Den?

141
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:55,720
Lair.

142
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,770
I imagined it differently.

143
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:03,050
Well, the little one keeps cleaning up in here.

144
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,540
She must enjoy it.

145
00:08:05,810 --> 00:08:06,490
Dad?

146
00:08:08,850 --> 00:08:09,950
Good, scar-face.

147
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:13,050
Why scar-face?

148
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:14,590
That's right, boy.

149
00:08:17,150 --> 00:08:18,050
Bull.

150
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:21,750
Sasa, leave us alone for a bit.

151
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:23,610
So bye bye.

152
00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:26,630
Not for a bit.

153
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:30,850
Stop talking back and scram, you redhead.

154
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:33,780
Go!

155
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:41,350
What is this supposed to mean?

156
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:45,450
Don't be surprised, I'm Bruiser Tom.

157
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,680
This place is kind of soft though.

158
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:52,800
That's on purpose.

159
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,150
So people don't know what I'm really like.

160
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:57,500
Awesome.

161
00:08:57,950 --> 00:08:59,880
Your handshake is impressive.

162
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,850
And your room is definitely bruiser-worthy.

163
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:06,150
You bet.

164
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:07,300
Scar-face.

165
00:09:09,450 --> 00:09:10,510
Sure.

166
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:14,120
That's where you keep your machete collection, right?

167
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,160
Yeah.

168
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:20,700
Bruiser, huh?

169
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:25,450
Iva, I promised Uncle Marek I'd take care of his kid.

170
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,100
Why are you acting like an idiot?

171
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,560
I resent that.

172
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:29,960
Sasa is scared of you now.

173
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:32,050
This is a little rascal.

174
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:35,050
And his old man wants me to make a tough guy out of him.

175
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:40,450
He wants his son to be a badass and entrusts him to a guy who's been asking me for two days when the bread pudding will be ready?

176
00:09:40,450 --> 00:09:42,050
Excuse me.

177
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:44,430
Today.

178
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:47,330
You're in for a surprise, Bruiser.

179
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:49,920
I didn't find the machetes.

180
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,600
But there's lots of hedgehogs.

181
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:55,250
I was wondering what kept stomping around in there.

182
00:09:55,550 --> 00:09:57,050
You only have enough for food, right?

183
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:58,070
Yeah.

184
00:09:59,090 --> 00:09:59,530
Awesome.

185
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:03,950
So for dinner, hedgehog soup or bread pudding, Bruiser Tom?

186
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,510
Hedgehog soup, hedgehog soup.

187
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:17,350
Were you playing hedgehog bowling?

188
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:18,730
Yeah, we had practice.

189
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:19,750
The league starts tomorrow.

190
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,670
Why didn't you say, I would've come.

191
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:22,750
This year I'm playing with Ziza.

192
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,510
With Ziza?

193
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:25,650
We always played together.

194
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:26,530
You're no fun to play with.

195
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:30,050
You lost two matches and in the fall you didn't even get new balls.

196
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:31,450
I can play with yours, right?

197
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:32,050
No, no, no.

198
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:33,650
Half a liter and they're still not for lending.

199
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,050
What are you writing?

200
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:40,150
Every wrong anyone's ever done to me.

201
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,060
I've been writing it since I was seven.

202
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:44,380
Just for insults about my nose I'm on my third notebook.

203
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,440
And why, it's not that bad.

204
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,250
What good will it do you?

205
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:51,650
One day I'll pay you all back with interest.

206
00:10:53,850 --> 00:10:54,850
That's quite a lot.

207
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:57,850
I'll be lucky if this notebook lasts me till the end of the year.

208
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:58,250
Yeah.

209
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:02,140
And I still have to add the list of people who'll forget my name day this year.

210
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:03,350
You have a name day?

211
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:10,450
Sashenka, you're bringing me a gift.

212
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,250
Here I am.

213
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:15,350
As long as it's not something from carrots, chestnuts or potatoes again.

214
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:23,450
Sasa, a potato.

215
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:33,150
Shh.

216
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,150
What do you say about the Bruiser here?

217
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:41,550
Bread pudding for a tough guy.

218
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:47,590
And this?

219
00:11:48,530 --> 00:11:49,130
What is it?

220
00:11:50,050 --> 00:11:51,250
Yum, tripe soup!

221
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:54,150
Made from onions!

222
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,240
Oh, sorry, Bruiser Tom.

223
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:00,180
I'm just an ordinary scar-face.

224
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:01,720
Should I flush it down the toilet?

225
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:02,800
Hold on.

226
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:06,030
Am I supposed to go hungry?

227
00:12:06,170 --> 00:12:08,270
There's plenty of soup, I made it from two hedgehogs.

228
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:09,710
Leave the soup for the little one then.

229
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:13,050
I'll just deal with this.

230
00:12:14,850 --> 00:12:16,850
Ugh, I wouldn't want that.

231
00:12:18,550 --> 00:12:23,550
Because you're still a little kid, but a man eats what there is.

232
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:26,530
Even if it were bu...

233
00:12:26,530 --> 00:12:27,650
Cream puffs with whipped cream.

234
00:12:29,850 --> 00:12:31,050
Or rice pudding?

235
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:32,650
Or.

236
00:12:32,650 --> 00:12:36,550
I know a guy who basically doesn't want anything else.

237
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:40,250
Wimp.

238
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:57,380
And since then everyone calls me Bruiser Tom.

239
00:12:57,950 --> 00:13:00,650
And is that killer dwarf still in the cellar?

240
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:04,890
Sure, I go beat him up every now and then to stay in shape.

241
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:08,250
Wow, Bruiser Tom, I wish I were like you.

242
00:13:09,950 --> 00:13:10,610
Everyone does.

243
00:13:10,850 --> 00:13:18,390
Bro, how come you're still up?

244
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,850
It's already half past ten.

245
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:27,850
Ozzak, this is Bull and I'm Bruiser Tom.

246
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:32,440
Your brother doesn't know you?

247
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:33,840
I'd say I know you both.

248
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:38,850
You're Bruiser Bull, you're Tom and I'm Ozzak and I'm hungry.

249
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:41,540
Not bread pudding again.

250
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:43,520
But I also had soup.

251
00:13:44,790 --> 00:13:45,390
What?

252
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:48,150
Spiney?

253
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:49,900
Prickly?

254
00:13:54,850 --> 00:13:55,850
Crybaby.

255
00:13:58,550 --> 00:13:59,650
Where are they both?

256
00:14:00,450 --> 00:14:00,950
Scar-face caught some fresh ones.

257
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:08,050
Come on, little guys, come rest.

258
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:10,740
How soft he is with your brother.

259
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:11,300
Right?

260
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:14,550
That's why I'm lending him my room tonight.

261
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:17,150
Let him toughen up a bit.

262
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,550
Sasa, it's open.

263
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,250
Don't worry, Dad's not here.

264
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:36,850
Iva, you have to help me.

265
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:38,810
She didn't like it?

266
00:14:38,810 --> 00:14:41,450
She didn't even look at it and said she doesn't want anything from carrots either.

267
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:43,450
You wouldn't have finished carving that flute anyway.

268
00:14:49,350 --> 00:14:50,610
But the child is cute.

269
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:51,590
Beautiful.

270
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,270
It would make me happy.

271
00:14:53,270 --> 00:14:53,610
Really?

272
00:14:53,950 --> 00:14:54,750
Very.

273
00:14:56,090 --> 00:14:56,570
Want it?

274
00:14:58,190 --> 00:14:58,710
Not really.

275
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:01,290
Okay then.

276
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,150
Thanks.

277
00:15:06,350 --> 00:15:07,850
Iva, I don't know what to do anymore.

278
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:10,140
Lexa is in the cellar and Mom is happy.

279
00:15:10,220 --> 00:15:12,340
Ugh, I'll never come up with anything that good.

280
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:13,700
Well, it is tough.

281
00:15:14,450 --> 00:15:15,480
I've had enough.

282
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:16,460
What are you going to do?

283
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:18,350
If I'm going to be the worst, then so be it.

284
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,750
What are you giving her?

285
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:20,580
A kitten.

286
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:22,780
Bold.

287
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,950
And if she doesn't want it, I'll keep it.

288
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,050
She won't flush it down the toilet?

289
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:30,750
Then I'll fish it out.

290
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:48,850
Yeah, he's doing twenty.

291
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:51,750
Twenty push-ups.

292
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:54,540
Twenty thousand push-ups.

293
00:15:54,850 --> 00:15:56,150
Like every day.

294
00:15:57,350 --> 00:15:58,150
I'll wait for him then.

295
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,550
I earned the strength badge.

296
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:10,250
Someone actually hit me in the cellar.

297
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:12,290
The killer dwarf.

298
00:16:12,290 --> 00:16:12,850
What?

299
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:15,350
But I already took care of him.

300
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:16,670
Awesome.

301
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:19,950
I'll stamp it for you.

302
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:23,250
Hey, a potato.

303
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,550
It looks like a butt.

304
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:26,790
Oh yeah.

305
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:30,850
Look, Bull, you shouldn't talk like that.

306
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:38,110
Iva, he's crying.

307
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:40,670
God, I didn't say that much.

308
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:48,750
Come here, there there, don't cry.

309
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:52,140
What are you doing?

310
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:52,480
What?

311
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:54,650
He's grabbing my butt.

312
00:16:55,570 --> 00:16:56,070
Whoa!

313
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:58,990
You little pervert!

314
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:02,080
What's going on here?

315
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,740
I've earned the touch badge.

316
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:05,840
Fine, fine, fine.

317
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:07,300
I'll sign it later.

318
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:12,080
Wow, he's really ripped.

319
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:15,550
He's done at least ten thousand already.

320
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:37,950
Why so quiet?

321
00:17:39,150 --> 00:17:42,250
When you have a minute, Bruiser, scar-face would like to talk to you.

322
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:45,650
Let's see what we've got here.

323
00:17:46,150 --> 00:17:48,650
I've got the touch badge, scar-face can confirm.

324
00:17:52,950 --> 00:17:56,580
I've got the style badge too, but the dwarf from the cellar disappeared.

325
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:58,060
Scar-face can confirm that too.

326
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,760
You were down there?

327
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:02,650
No, I ran into the dwarf with a black eye.

328
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,520
Iva, help me out!

329
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,640
Grab a hedgehog and come on!

330
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,020
Astrid, you know I don't play.

331
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:07,760
You have to!

332
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,840
Old Gut's hedgehog slipped out of his hand and hit Ziza right in the eye!

333
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:11,440
Oh God!

334
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,200
Luckily with its snout, so he'll still see.

335
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:15,380
But we were already eight teams from the final, come on!

336
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,080
Astrid, sorry, they really can't, they have fleas.

337
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:20,600
Iva, you know I've been looking forward to hedgehog bowling all winter.

338
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:21,640
What's hedgehog bowling?

339
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:23,500
They bowl using hedgehogs.

340
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:24,820
I want to play too!

341
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:25,320
Sure!

342
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:28,260
Until you can hold a hedgehog in your bare hand for 10 minutes, you can't play.

343
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:28,460
Eek!

344
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:31,860
Who?

345
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:33,620
Me, obviously.

346
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:37,680
Look, hedgehog bowling is too soft for me.

347
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:38,120
What?

348
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:40,750
You always said you don't like how they whimper.

349
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:43,200
Bruiser, you'll be great, you'll crush them.

350
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,400
Sure, bro, let's go.

351
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:45,640
Alright.

352
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:49,050
Let's go hedgehog bowling, hedgehog bowling!

353
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:55,350
Hey Bruiser, if I win, I'll run upstairs to Stodola's and ask for some of his snakes.

354
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,390
I'll cook them for dinner.

355
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:56,970
Awesome.

356
00:18:57,530 --> 00:18:59,310
Whoa, there are even snakes here.

357
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,400
Let's go.

358
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:01,800
Let's go.

359
00:19:14,450 --> 00:19:16,420
And here we'll drink to it, Bull.

360
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:18,040
We didn't even make the final.

361
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:19,620
But Bruiser played great.

362
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,820
Yeah, he played a nice floater.

363
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:24,120
Spiney opened up mid-air and hit the referee with her quills.

364
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,660
And you'll have a drink too.

365
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:27,780
You bet.

366
00:19:29,850 --> 00:19:30,950
Hi, Tomas.

367
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:34,050
Ozzak took me hedgehog bowling today.

368
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:36,650
Ozzak?

369
00:19:37,150 --> 00:19:38,950
Didn't you say you'd never go with me again?

370
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:42,750
It's nice here.

371
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:43,530
What's this place called?

372
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,350
Nothing yet.

373
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:47,850
They could name it after you.

374
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:51,250
The Toucan.

375
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:55,150
I don't have any damn room here anymore.

376
00:20:15,430 --> 00:20:16,330
Hey, come in.

377
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:18,860
Got any kind of box?

378
00:20:18,860 --> 00:20:21,250
I've got the gift already but I'm afraid it'll chew through the bag.

379
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:22,620
Some little kitten?

380
00:20:22,850 --> 00:20:24,750
They were out of cats, they only had cat food left.

381
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:25,950
Food?

382
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:26,700
Mice.

383
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,480
Well good, she won't like a mouse either.

384
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:32,280
I don't like it either, it's got this bald little tail.

385
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:33,740
You can throw it away later.

386
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,210
Look, this is all I've got.

387
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:37,750
It won't suffocate in there?

388
00:20:37,850 --> 00:20:42,470
Relax, Bruiser Tom couldn't open one once, so she poked a hole in the lid.

389
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:47,750
And could you hold it by the tail?

390
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:52,170
Sure, I'm Bruiser's scar-face, I cook hedgehogs.

391
00:20:52,550 --> 00:20:54,450
Why wouldn't I grab a mouse by the tail, right?

392
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:07,420
Couldn't I just leave it here?

393
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:26,150
You didn't have to get up, you know.

394
00:21:27,150 --> 00:21:28,650
Breakfast for tough guys.

395
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:32,750
Bull isn't up yet?

396
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:35,850
He said he's going to the cellar to check on the dwarf.

397
00:21:43,150 --> 00:21:44,750
Oh God, hello, Mr. Stodola.

398
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:46,810
Bull?

399
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:49,250
The boy said he's staying with you.

400
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:50,750
Did something happen?

401
00:21:51,850 --> 00:21:53,650
No, but it could have.

402
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:57,740
That little rascal climbed through the skylight all the way up.

403
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:59,140
What's the meaning of this, Bull?

404
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:00,960
I was earning the courage badge.

405
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:03,360
And you broke into someone's apartment?

406
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:05,480
This isn't a courage badge.

407
00:22:05,650 --> 00:22:06,840
This is a proper spanking.

408
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,140
Well, don't be too hard on him.

409
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:10,760
Luckily nothing happened.

410
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:13,000
Even though I do have some venomous ones up there.

411
00:22:14,850 --> 00:22:16,620
Neighbor, I'm so sorry, I...

412
00:22:17,850 --> 00:22:23,550
Look, we snake people have a saying: if you don't padlock your skylight, you're asking for trouble.

413
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:26,750
And thanks to this young man, I've now padlocked it.

414
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:28,350
Take care.

415
00:22:34,850 --> 00:22:41,450
Bull, you know very well that Bruiser Tom is the last person who'd forbid you from playing with snakes.

416
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,120
What is it?

417
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:49,550
Nothing, I just remembered a certain guy who ran from a grass snake in the Tatras.

418
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:57,860
Breaking into strangers' apartments isn't brave.

419
00:22:57,860 --> 00:22:58,280
No.

420
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:01,850
But catching a snake with your bare hands is brave.

421
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:02,670
Yeah.

422
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:06,050
Dad said you killed a reindeer with a snake.

423
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:09,110
Well, yeah actually.

424
00:23:09,110 --> 00:23:11,250
So you had to catch it with your bare hands.

425
00:23:11,450 --> 00:23:13,550
Well, I didn't have anything better at hand.

426
00:23:14,450 --> 00:23:15,750
So that was brave.

427
00:23:16,990 --> 00:23:18,290
Actually, you're right.

428
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:19,410
Awesome.

429
00:23:58,600 --> 00:23:59,240
Well, sorry about that.

430
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:07,150
Wow, Bruiser Tom.

431
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:08,660
What?

432
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:14,040
Hitting a guy in the head with a snake, that's pretty badass.

433
00:24:14,350 --> 00:24:15,050
Thanks, Bull.

434
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:22,690
I beat up the dwarf in the cellar.

435
00:24:22,690 --> 00:24:24,330
When we go down I'll show you.

436
00:24:24,410 --> 00:24:26,790
And the snake was so big and it was hissing at me.

437
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:27,970
And Bruiser Tom caught it.

438
00:24:27,990 --> 00:24:28,990
And I think he was already strangling it.

439
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:30,410
And then he threw it into the room.

440
00:24:30,810 --> 00:24:32,170
Bruiser Tom and the snake.

441
00:24:32,550 --> 00:24:33,150
Yeah, he's awesome.

442
00:24:33,150 --> 00:24:35,250
He eats everything, even with onions.

443
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:38,250
That's true.

444
00:24:38,410 --> 00:24:38,930
Yeah.

445
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:41,590
Just, he didn't actually strangle the snake.

446
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:42,990
He's looking for it now with Mr. Stodola.

447
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:49,550
Maybe he really did have things under control at that party with Zazvorkova.

448
00:24:50,820 --> 00:24:51,740
Well, well, well.

449
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:57,180
As we snake people say, where the hedgehog is king, the snake meets its end.

450
00:24:57,180 --> 00:24:58,600
What if it's still alive?

451
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,840
It's just hiding somewhere.

452
00:25:02,450 --> 00:25:04,350
I'll just grab it.

453
00:25:05,250 --> 00:25:06,270
And eat it!

454
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:08,010
Yeah, Bruiser, that's the spirit.

455
00:25:09,330 --> 00:25:11,170
I'm not listening to this.

456
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:16,170
Marek, you're here already?

457
00:25:16,170 --> 00:25:16,970
Yeah, hey.

458
00:25:17,930 --> 00:25:19,670
Sounds like you had a great time.

459
00:25:19,670 --> 00:25:22,610
Yeah, this kid might actually become a man one day.

460
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:25,110
I think you should take him more often.

461
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:25,330
No.

462
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:30,330
A real man has to be able to take care of his own kid himself.

463
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:31,530
Right, Bruiser.

464
00:25:33,650 --> 00:25:34,350
Yeah, yeah.

465
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:35,750
OK.

466
00:25:36,450 --> 00:25:37,350
Is that cocoa?

467
00:25:38,450 --> 00:25:39,880
No, it's, it's...

468
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:40,120
Yeah!

469
00:25:41,850 --> 00:25:43,450
It's cocoa.

470
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:46,150
Maybe I should start drinking it too.

471
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:50,550
That would make you really tough, Bull.

472
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:03,680
Mom, I'm bringing your name day gift.

473
00:26:04,350 --> 00:26:05,750
Hold on, let me find your page.

474
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:13,910
Sasa, pea violin, potato trumpet, chestnut castanets.

475
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:14,430
Come in.

476
00:26:16,850 --> 00:26:19,250
You won't like it, but I don't care.

477
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:25,650
Well, Sasa, you really outdid yourself.

478
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:25,950
Yeah.

479
00:26:30,450 --> 00:26:32,950
I'm done with that cellar, someone keeps hitting me down there.

480
00:26:33,050 --> 00:26:36,600
Lexa, now that Sasa outdid herself, you have to step up.

481
00:26:36,950 --> 00:26:38,050
How did she outdo herself?

482
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:40,850
She gave me a snake.

483
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:52,350
Well, if I'd known that, I would've gotten one ages ago.
